# Authentication


## Create session


### Resource

`<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>/auth/sign_in`


### URL parameters

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------


### Query String

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------


### HTTP request method

`POST`


### HTTP headers

Key | Value
--------- | -----------
Content-Type | application/json; charset=utf-8


### HTTP body

{ "email": "email", "password": "password" }


### Note

1. For every new HTTP request to another reosource, we use:
   1. New `access-token` retrieved from a HTTP response;
   1. Rest reciveced headers which wer recived during the creating the session without modifing them. Read more [here](https://github.com/lynndylanhurley/devise_token_auth/blob/master/docs/security.md).

> HTTP example request

```http
POST <%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>/auth/sign_in
```

```http
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
```

```json
{
  "email": "user@<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>",
  "password": "password"
}
```


> HTTP response 200 OK

```http
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
access-token: tzrxsp92jig88A7mUeUKlA
token-type: Bearer
client: VOSa5JraNO9_9fuuWUXs3w
uid: user@<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>
```

```json
{
  "data": {
    "id": 1,
    "deactivated": false,
    "email": "user@<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>",
    "provider": "email",
    "roles": [
      "administrator"
    ],
    "uid": "user@<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>",
    "first_name": "admin",
    "last_name": "1",
    "login": "user",
    "allow_password_change": false
  }
}
```


> HTTP response 401 Unauthorized

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "errors": [
    "Invalid login credentials. Please try again."
  ]
}
```


## Destroy session


### Resource

`<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>/auth/sign_out`


### URL parameters

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------


### Query String

Parameter | Description
--------- | -----------


### HTTP request method

`DELETE`


### HTTP headers

Key | Value
--------- | -----------
Content-Type | application/json; charset=utf-8
access-token | xxxyyyzzz
token-type | Bearer
client | xxxyyyzzz
uid | email


### HTTP body


> HTTP example request

```http
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
access-token: tzrxsp92jig88A7mUeUKlA
token-type: Bearer
client: VOSa5JraNO9_9fuuWUXs3w
uid: user@<%= ENV['DOMAIN_NAME'] %>
```


> HTTP response 200 OK

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```


> HTTP response 404 Not Found

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "errors": [
    "User was not found or was not logged in."
  ]
}
```
